{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"40ca381c-aee2-4f43-bf00-fc223886bbca","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for adding RAG-based Q&A to your .NET 10 Web API:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  Markdown   │──────▶│  Ingestion Svc   │──────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  Docs/      │       │  (chunk+embed)   │       │  (in-memory or │\n└─────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       │   external DB) │\n                                                  └───────┬────────┘\n┌─────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐               │\n│  User Query │──────▶│  Query Endpoint  │───similarity──▶│\n│  POST /ask  │       │  (embed → search │◀──top-K chunks─┘\n└─────────────┘       │   → LLM answer)  │\n                      └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Suggested Package |\n|-------|---------------|-------------------|\n| **Chunking** | Split markdown by heading/paragraph into ~300–500 token chunks with overlap | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` or custom splitter |\n| **Embeddings** | Convert chunks → vectors | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` (OpenAI/Azure OpenAI embedding model) |\n| **Vector Store** | Store & search embeddings by cosine similarity | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` + in-memory provider (swap for Qdrant/Azure AI Search later) |\n| **LLM Completion** | Generate grounded answer from top-K chunks + user question | Azure OpenAI / OpenAI via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n| **API Surface** | `POST /ingest` (trigger re-index), `POST /ask` (query) | ASP.NET Controllers |\n\n---\n\n## Proposed Flow\n\n### Ingestion (`POST /ingest`)\n1. Enumerate `Docs/*.md` files\n2. Split each file into overlapping chunks (heading-aware)\n3. Generate embeddings for each chunk\n4. Upsert into vector store with metadata (source file, heading)\n\n### Query (`POST /ask`)\n1. Embed the user's question\n2. Retrieve top-K (e.g., 5) nearest chunks from vector store\n3. Build a prompt: system instruction + retrieved chunks + user question\n4. Call LLM for a grounded answer\n5. Return answer + source citations\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure (planned)\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Controllers/\n│   ├── IngestController.cs\n│   └── AskController.cs\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentChunker.cs\n│   ├── EmbeddingService.cs\n│   ├── VectorStoreService.cs\n│   └── QAService.cs\n├── Models/\n│   ├── AskRequest.cs\n│   ├── AskResponse.cs\n│   └── DocumentChunk.cs\n├── Docs/\n├── Program.cs\n└── appsettings.json  (API keys, model config)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Needed\n- **OpenAI/Azure OpenAI** endpoint + API key (for embeddings & completions)\n- Chunk size / overlap parameters\n- Top-K retrieval count\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions to Confirm\n1. **Vector store**: Start in-memory (simplest) or external (Qdrant, Azure AI Search)?\n2. **Embedding model**: `text-embedding-3-small` (cheap) vs `text-embedding-3-large` (better)?\n3. **LLM model**: `gpt-4o` or `gpt-4o-mini`?\n4. **Auth**: Should `/ask` and `/ingest` require authentication?\n\nLet me know your preferences on these choices, or say **\"implement it\"** and I'll build it with sensible defaults (in-memory store, `text-embedding-3-small`, `gpt-4o-mini`, no auth).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"028d48e9-b112-4f2f-930e-2e7c53331f2b","outputTokens":1000,"requestId":"2C04:22188A:182DF73:1B50D22:69FD4499"},"id":"6258528a-4169-4146-a3b7-5b04ea458fe1","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:04:30.037Z","parentId":"daddaebc-7e7a-4ae5-8823-a441a964666e"}
